@liorn, @awestendorf: per https://www.rabbitmq.com/heartbeats.html

> Heartbeat frames are sent about every timeout / 2 seconds. After two missed heartbeats, the peer is considered to be unreachable. 

Is this change compatible with it?

I would make this simpler by updating `getCommandLineOption()` to handle `None`. Then you could just make it:

```
if getCommandLineOption("debug", cmdOptions):
    ...
else if getCommandLineOption("optimizations-native", cmdOptions):
    ...
else if getCommandLineOption("optimizations-lto", cmdOptions):
    ...
```

How about something like this, which isn't quite python code exactly, and really sloppy even if it were


    elif re.match(r'(\^\S+?\$)', spec) as m:
        first = m.group()
        operator = spec[m.end()] if len(spec) > m.end() else None
        if operator is None:
            self.spec = first
            self.regex = re.compile(spec)
            self.match = self.regex_match_
        else:
            return VersionSpec((operator, tuple(first, spec[m.end()+1:])))

I would recommend something like:
```Python
if not for_scale_set:
  subnet_match = next((...), None)
else:
   subnet_matches = [...]
   for s in subnet_matches:
      ...
      if _subnet_capacity_check(...):
        subnet_match = s
        break
```
There's no reason to do the whole list comprehension for a regular VM if you're just going to take the first.  Also, I don't think you need `if subnet_matches:` because if there are no matches you should still get an empty list. If you don't, you could also just say `for s in subnet_matches or []:`.

