For this one, you'll want to mock `github.authenticate` using a sinon spy.

```
const mockGithub = sinon.spy(github, 'authenticate');

// Call into the reducer with your action

// Check that your spy/stub was called with the right args
expect(mockGithub).to.have.been.calledWith({ type: 'oauth', token: 'TOKEN' });

// Check that the state set your new github object
// which means you'll need a sinon stub instead
```

Wouldn't it be more logical to remove all the conditionals and flag-setting from the ``init_holder_helper``s and rewrite this function as:

```
auto inst = (instance_type *) inst_;
if (inst->owned)
    init_holder_helper(inst, (const holder_type *) holder_ptr, inst->value);
inst->constructed = true;
```

The default should be handled in one place only, if it's the `Plugin` base class it might be better do something like this: 
```python
def stream_title(self):
    title = self._get_title()
    if title is not None:
        return title
    else:
        return self.url

def _get_title(self):
    return None
```
And the `DEFAULT_PLAYER_ARGUMENTS`/`create_format_args` stuff should be refactored. 

side note: to clarify; the `streams` method is the public method for getting the streams, it normalises the result of `_get_streams`. `Plugin` subclasses _must_ implement `_get_streams`.

Then maybe the following could be better.

